TITLE.P: Framework agreement for temporary staff services — Award of contract notice

SHORT_DESCR.P: DIFI has entered into several parallel framework agreements for temporary staff services on behalf of 18 government entities. The aim of the framework agreement is to cover the entities' need for temporary staff services in different temporary staff categories and in different geographical areas.
The Contracting Authority needs temporary staff services in the following jobs:
— switchboard/reception,
— secretary,
— archive employees,
— HR-employees,
— communication,
— ICT employees,
— user support/user service.
The list is not exhaustive. There can be a need for other types of competence in this job category.
We would like to enter into a contract with up to 3 tenderers for this job category.
See Annex 1 of the framework agreement for further details.
The Contracting Authority needs temporary staff services in the following jobs:
— Controller/Financial consultant,
— accounting employee,
— payroll employees.
The list is not exhaustive. There can be a need for other types of competence in this job category.
We would like to enter into a contract with up to 3 tenderers for this job category.
See Annex 1 of the framework agreement for further details.
The Contracting Authority needs temporary staff services in the following jobs:
— nurses,
— pharmacists,
— bioengineers,
— temporary staff for various forms of laboratory work.
e.g. laboratory technicians and various engineering qualifications, depending on that type of laboratory work is to be carried out.
The list is not exhaustive. There can be a need for other types of competence in this job category.
We would like to enter into 3 contracts for this job category.
See Annex 1 of the framework agreement for further details.
The Contracting Authority needs temporary staff services in the following jobs:
— canteen/kitchen employees,
— cleaners.
The list is not exhaustive. There can be a need for other types of competence in this job category.
We would like to enter into 3 contracts for this job category.
See Annex 1 of the framework agreement for further details.
In this lot we require temporary staff services in the following categories:
1. administrative positions;
2. finance and accounts;
3. canteen/cleaning.
See Annex 1 for detailed information on the job categories.
A framework agreement will be signed with up to 3 total tenderers.
In this lot we require temporary staff services in the following categories:
1. administrative positions;
2. finance and accounts;
3. canteen/cleaning.
See Annex 1 for detailed information on the job categories. The greatest need for temporary staff is in Categories 1 and 2.
A framework agreement will be signed with up to 3 total tenderers.
